text: Ecaterina Oancia (25 March 1954 - 3 December 2024) was a Romanian rowing cox. She was born in Sângeorgiu de Pădure, Romania. Oancia won a gold medal at the 1984 Summer Olympics and a silver medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics.
